articles.title: More than 100 arrested in Georgia protests after government puts EU hopes on ice - CNN
articles.description: Georgia’s interior ministry has said that 107 people were arrested during Friday’s protests in the capital Tbilisi sparked by the government’s decision to delay the former Soviet country’s bid to join the European Union.
